{"conversation_id":"98c15930-aed8-42e3-a7e1-f35db8c45bd0","generation_id":"346c7189-e752-494c-b816-54cf6cef5679","model":"gpt-5.2-codex-high","tool_name":"WebFetch","tool_input":{"url":"https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview"},"tool_output":"{\"status\":\"success\",\"url\":\"https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview\",\"content_length\":4300,\"content\":\"Nano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview) - API, Providers, Stats\\n# Google: Nano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview)\\n### [google](https://openrouter.ai/google)/gemini-3-pro-image-preview\\n[Chat](https://openrouter.ai/chat?models=google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview)[Compare](https://openrouter.ai/compare/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview)\\nCreatedNov 20, 202565,536context\\n$2/M input tokens$12/M output tokens$120/M tokens$2/M audio tokens\\nNano Banana Pro is Google’s most advanced image-generation and editing model, built on Gemini 3 Pro. It extends the original Nano Banana with significantly improved multimodal reasoning, real-world grounding, and high-fidelity visual synthesis. The model generates context-rich graphics, from infographics and diagrams to cinematic composites, and can incorporate real-time information via Search grounding.\\nIt offers industry-leading text rendering in images (including long passages and multilingual layouts), consistent multi-image blending, and accurate identity preservation across up to five subjects. Nano Banana Pro adds fine-grained creative controls such as localized edits, lighting and focus adjustments, camera transformations, and support for 2K/4K outputs and flexible aspect ratios. It is designed for professional-grade design, product visualization, storyboarding, and complex multi-element compositions while remaining efficient for general image creation workflows.\\n[Chat](https://openrouter.ai/chat?models=google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview)[Compare](https://openrouter.ai/compare/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview)\\nStandard\\nOverview\\nProviders\\nPerformance\\nApps\\nActivity\\nUptime\\nQuickstart\\n## Providers for Nano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview)[](https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview/providers)\\n### OpenRouter[routes requests](https://openrouter.ai/docs/provider-routing)to the best providers that are able to handle your prompt size and parameters, with fallbacks to maximize[uptime](https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview/uptime).\\n## Performance for Nano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview)[](https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview/performance)\\n### Compare different providers across OpenRouter\\nAll locations\\nSorting API Example\\n## Apps using Nano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview)[](https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview/apps)\\n### Top public apps this month\\n## Recent activity on Nano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview)[](https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview/activity)\\n### Total usage per day on OpenRouter\\nPrompt\\n60.3M\\nCompletion\\n46.4M\\nReasoning\\n13M\\nPrompt tokens measure input size. Reasoning tokens show internal thinking before a response. Completion tokens reflect total output length.\\n## Uptime stats for Nano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview)[](https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview/uptime)\\n### Uptime stats forNano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview)across all providers\\n## Sample code and API for Nano Banana Pro (Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview)[](https://openrouter.ai/google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview/api)\\n### OpenRouter normalizes requests and responses across providers for you.\\n[Create API key](https://openrouter.ai/settings/keys)\\nOpenRouter supports image generation through models that have`image`in their output modalities. These models can create images from text prompts when you specify`modalities: [&quot;image&quot;, &quot;text&quot;]`in your request. The generated images are returned as base64-encoded data URLs in the assistant message.[Learn more about image generation](https://openrouter.ai/docs/features/multimodal/image-generation).\\nIn the examples below, the[OpenRouter-specific headers](https://openrouter.ai/docs/requests#request-headers)are optional. Setting them allows your app to appear on the OpenRouter leaderboards.\\n## Using third-party SDKs\\nFor information about using third-party SDKs and frameworks with OpenRouter, please see our[frameworks documentation](https://openrouter.ai/docs/guides/community/frameworks-and-integrations-overview).\\nSee the[Request docs](https://openrouter.ai/docs/api-reference/overview)for all possible fields, and[Parameters](https://openrouter.ai/docs/api-reference/parameters)for explanations of specific sampling parameters.\"}","duration":13247,"tool_use_id":"call_w647Z2On9uAVg4HNAaZ4IVvb\nfc_02b3fbb4cc49ae830169837c96fd9081959a82460104eabceb","hook_event_name":"postToolUse","cursor_version":"2026.01.28-fd13201","workspace_roots":["/home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools"],"user_email":"brian@lonestartrade.com","transcript_path":"/home/blgroce/.cursor/projects/home-blgroce-tools-cli-tools/agent-transcripts/98c15930-aed8-42e3-a7e1-f35db8c45bd0.txt"}
